id: pm-vcu7
title: "Annotation --add silently stores flag-like tokens as content: pm notes <id> --add --stdin records the literal note \"--stdin\""
description: "Found live during ecosystem audit #11 (2026-07-06): an agent invoked pm notes pm-doxj --add --stdin (copying comments' --stdin flag) and the CLI silently stored the string --stdin as the note text on the roadmap milestone. Option values beginning with -- are almost never intended content for annotation commands. Duplicate check 2026-07-06: pm-gdi7 covers UNKNOWN-option suggestions (different failure: here the option is known and the VALUE is a swallowed flag); pm-yql1 is facet grammar consolidation; pm-jkjt/GH-450 is the analogous silent-wrong-data class for durations; searched 'stdin', 'flag value', annotation issues — no existing item."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli",data-quality,dogfood
created_at: "2026-07-06T13:25:17.483Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-06T19:57:28.470Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "Annotation/value-taking flags (--add on notes/learnings, comment text sources, --message, etc.) reject or explicitly confirm values that start with '-' unless separated by '=' or preceded by '--' terminator; error names the correct stdin spelling for the command (notes/learnings: --add - ; comments: --stdin); regression tests cover notes --add --stdin, learnings --add --file, comments --add --stdin; contracts/docs updated if flag semantics change"
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: fixed
expected_result: Annotation add paths reject likely swallowed flags while keeping explicit literal dash-leading text writable.
actual_result: "Notes/learnings/comments reject flag-like --add values with command-specific stdin guidance, while text=--value and real stdin inputs remain accepted."
