close_reason: "Implemented shared annotation guard for flag-like --add values with command-specific stdin guidance and text= escape hatch; verified focused tests, full 100% coverage, type/lint/audit gates, and installed-tarball dogfood evidence."
body: "## Repro (live, 2026.7.6)\nPM_AUTHOR=maintainer-agent pm notes pm-doxj --add --stdin <<'EOF'\nreal note text\nEOF\nResult: note created with text '--stdin'; the heredoc content is discarded. Exit 0, no warning.\n\n## Why it matters\nSilent wrong data in the tracker (same class as GH-450 duration months bug). The agent believes the note was recorded; the actual content is lost. Because notes are append-only (no --edit/--delete, unlike comments), recovery required manual .toon surgery + history-chain revert — see companion parity task filed the same session.\n\n## Cause\ncommander option --add <text> consumes the next token as its value; createStdinTokenResolver only special-cases the exact token '-'. Any other flag-like token ('--stdin', '--file', a typoed flag) becomes content.\n\n## Suggested fix\nIn parseAnnotationTextInput / the shared annotation command path (src/cli/commands/annotation-command.ts, src/core/item/parse.ts), reject values matching ^--?[a-z] with a structured error that (a) shows the swallowed token, (b) lists the command's real input sources incl. the stdin spelling, (c) mentions quoting or 'text=' explicit-key form for genuinely dash-leading content. Keep an escape hatch (text=--stdin explicit key form) so legitimate dash-leading content stays writable."
